      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Swapping a capacitor, while sometimes portrayed as simple in videos, is a task that requires a good understanding of electrical principles, even when the power is off. It's not as straightforward as just swapping out a bad piece of junk for a new one, especially if you don't know the exact specifications of the original. For safety, and because these capacitors can store a dangerous charge even when disconnected, it's best to let a qualified HVAC technician handle the replacement.",
